Residents began assessing the damage to their homes and property caused by a furious flash flood that killed at least 11 and left many homeless.
A police officer said that whole families were lost.
Downtown Shadyside was the center of rescue operations.
The tremendous flood damage was to the outskirts of town where small tractors and four-wheel-drive vehicles were the only means of transportation.
Several residents recounted their personal losses.
At least 170 members of the Ohio National Guard were brought in to patrol and to help rebuild roads washed out by the floods.
Curious sightseers jammed highways leading into the stricken area. 
